$$
\begin{aligned}
\frac{1+2\text{i}}{{{(1+\text{i})}^{2}}} &= \frac{(1+2\text{i})(1-\text{i})}{(1+\text{i})(1+\text{i})(1-\text{i})} \\
&= \frac{1+2\text{i}-\text{i}-2{{\text{i}}^{2}}}{1-{{\text{i}}^{2}}} \\
&= \frac{1+\text{i}}{2} \\
&= \frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{2}\text{i}
\end{aligned}
$$
因此，答案是D：$1+\frac{1}{2}\text{i}$。
